column5: Anyone up there have any idea what the surface temps on LOTW are right now?
I talked to a friend that owns a resort on Whitefish Bay the water temp was approximately 44 degrees today, so I would think the darker water would be 4-6 degrees warmer. BOB

The outflow of lake of the woods at Kenora is 46 F as of today. The mouth of the Rainy is a little warmer than that at 47. Back bays will be warmer but the main basin of the lake should be close to that. We are supposed to get a good frost tonight and the next three days are below average temps.
48.7 f southwest of Kenora North of Whisky, West of Scotty, East of Wolfhttp://www.ndbc.noaa.gov/station_page.php?station=45148
Miles Bay is runnning 50-52 most places.
